\backslash
end{definition}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From now on, given any 
\begin_inset Formula $A\in SDD_{n}$
\end_inset

, we will implicitly define a Laplacian 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{A}$
\end_inset

 associated to it, using the augmented Laplacian.
 This process is also reversible and can be used to define a matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{A}\in SDD_{n}$
\end_inset

 from 
\begin_inset Formula $L_{A}$
\end_inset

 with appealing properties in a very simple way.
 We call this process 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

floating
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 of the Laplacian, by opposition to 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

grounding
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 the SDD matrix as a Laplacian.
 
\end_layout

